text: Dilara Eltemur is a Turkish karateka. In 2018, she won one of the bronze medals in the women's team kumite event at the 2018 World Karate Championships held in Madrid, Spain. At the 2018 European Karate Championships held in Novi Sad, Serbia, she won one of the bronze medals in both the individual and team kata events. In 2019, she represented Turkey at the 2019 European Games in Minsk, Belarus and she won one of the bronze medals in the women's individual kata event.
